{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Known for one of the strictest home-school laws in the nation, Pennsylvania has relaxed some requirements, and that has brought it to the forefront in a lobbying war.", "abstract": "More families are choosing to home school their children, even as regulation of the practice has diminished nationwide; some parents are choosing to flee the testing and curriculums that have come along with new Common Core standards; Pennsylvania is latest state to have loosened oversight of home schooling, removing requirement that parents submit portfolios of work and allowing them to issue homegrown high school diplomas.", "section_name": "Education", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Motoko", "role": "reported", "lastname": "RICH", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By MOTOKO RICH", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/05/education/home-schooling-more-pupils-less-regulation.html", "lead_paragraph": "Known for one of the strictest home-school laws in the nation, Pennsylvania has relaxed some requirements, and that has brought it to the forefront in a lobbying war.", "headline": {"main": "Home Schooling: More Pupils, Less Regulation ", "print_headline": "Home Schooling: More Pupils, Less Regulation"}, "_id": "54a9fbd638f0d80bc9594128", "word_count": "1609", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/01/04/us/20150105_HOMESCHOOL-slide-WYGS/20150105_HOMESCHOOL-slide-WYGS-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/01/04/us/20150105_HOMESCHOOL-slide-WYGS/20150105_HOMESCHOOL-slide-WYGS-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2015/01/04/us/20150105_HOMESCHOOL-slide-WYGS/20150105_HOMESCHOOL-slide-WYGS-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/01/04/us/20150105_HOMESCHOOL-slide-WYGS/20150105_HOMESCHOOL-slide-WYGS-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth":